The statement by Lisa O. Monaco, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, reflects on the third anniversary of the Boston Marathon bombings. She remembers the victims of the attack and honors the first responders who provided aid and comfort. Monaco also expresses gratitude for the men and women who fight for freedom and secure the homeland. She acknowledges that the violence has forever affected many families, but emphasizes that the spirit of freedom will triumph over fear. Monaco draws inspiration from the resilience of the city of Boston, which has shown the true meaning of being "Boston Strong."